"Climate Change Adaptation: A Review" &#x20;

One. Introduction

This paper is a review of climate change adaptation. It references six peer-reviewed articles. As climate change affects ecosystems and human societies, trees (Smith et al., 2018) are shifting and potential food shortages are worsening (Johnson, 2019). Rising sea levels and more frequent hurricanes cause concerns (Joyce, 2020), threatening cities (Christensen, 2020 & Wang, 2021). Adaptation is crucial to mitigate its impacts (Rodriguez, 2017).

Some of the most critical peer-reviewed sources on climate change adaptation include: 
1. Adger et al. (2013); 
2. IPCC (2013); 
3. IPCC (2014a); 
4. IPCC (2014b); 
5. Banerjee et al. (2015);

